article.description: — KJ Williams had 21 points and 11 rebounds as Murray State stretched its win streak to eight games, rolling past Tennessee Tech 79-53 on Monday night.
article.headline: Williams lifts Murray St. past Tennessee Tech 79-53
article.linkText: Williams lifts Murray St. past Tennessee Tech 79-53
article.story: MURRAY, Ky. -- — KJ Williams had 21 points and 11 rebounds as Murray State stretched its win streak to eight games, rolling past Tennessee Tech 79-53 on Monday night. Tevin Brown had 14 points, six rebounds and six assists for Murray State (18-2, 8-0 Ohio Valley Conference). Justice Hill added 11 points. Daniel Ramsey had 12 points for the Golden Eagles (5-13, 2-3).
